NAME
    gzip - compress or expand files

SYNOPSIS
    gzip [OPTION]... [FILE]...
    gunzip [OPTION]... [FILE]...
    zcat [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
    gzip reduces the size of files using Lempel-Ziv coding (LZ77). By
    default, each file is replaced by a compressed version with the
    extension '.gz', preserving ownership, mode, and timestamps.

    gunzip decompresses files. It is equivalent to gzip -d. zcat is
    equivalent to gunzip -c.

    When no FILE is given, or FILE is '-', read from standard input and
    write to standard output.

OPTIONS
    -c, --stdout, --to-stdout
        Write output to standard output; keep original files unchanged.

    -d, --decompress, --uncompress
        Decompress the given files.

    -f, --force
        Force compression or decompression even if the output file
        already exists or if the file has multiple hard links.

    -k, --keep
        Keep (do not delete) input files after compression.

    -l, --list
        For each compressed file, list compressed and uncompressed sizes,
        compression ratio, and uncompressed file name.

    -n, --no-name
        Do not save or restore the original file name and timestamp.

    -N, --name
        Save the original file name and timestamp (default).

    -q, --quiet
        Suppress all warnings.

    -r, --recursive
        Traverse directory structure; compress all files found.

    -t, --test
        Test the compressed file integrity.

    -v, --verbose
        Verbose; display compression ratio for each file.

    -1, --fast
        Compress faster (less compression, level 1).

    -9, --best
        Compress better (slower, level 9). Default is -6.

    --version
        Output version information and exit.

    --help
        Display help and exit.

EXAMPLES
    gzip file.txt
        Compress file.txt to file.txt.gz; remove original.

    gzip -k file.txt
        Compress but keep original file.

    gzip -d file.txt.gz
        Decompress file.txt.gz.

    gzip -c file.txt > file.txt.gz
        Compress to stdout.

    gunzip -c archive.gz | grep error
        Decompress to stdout and pipe to grep.

    gzip -r logs/
        Recursively compress all files in logs/.

    gzip -l *.gz
        List compression statistics for all .gz files.

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success.
    1   Error occurred.
